text.section:
All requests for use of state aircraft shall be approved in advance by the:
Constitutional officer;
Program cabinet secretary or his designee in writing;
For the judicial branch, the Chief Justice of the Supreme Court or the director of the Administrative Office of the Courts; or
For the legislative branch, the co-chairs of the Legislative Research Commission or the director of the Legislative Research Commission.

All requests for use of state aircraft shall be submitted on a form prescribed by the Capital City Airport Division and shall contain at a minimum the following information:
Cabinet or agency name;
Department name with appropriate billing account number;
Purpose of the trip;
Destination, including any planned stopovers and the reason for them;
Names of all passengers on the flight; and
Identification of any percentage of the flight that is for personal business in cases of the Governor or Lieutenant Governor as allowed under KRS 174.506.
